body:
This problem comes from the commit that closes this issue: https://github.com/libgdx/libgdx/issues/2368

This code causes a crash:

``` java
public String toString () {
        return data.fontFile.nameWithoutExtension();
    }
```

The field data.fontFile is null when using a Freetype font loaded from the AssetManager.

Test code for this is as follows:

``` java
public void create () {
        batch = new SpriteBatch();
        img = new Texture("badlogic.jpg");

        assetManager=new AssetManager();

        // Get a file handle resolver for internal files, since all of these
        // should be internal files
        FileHandleResolver resolver = new InternalFileHandleResolver();

        // set the manager to load freetype files and bitmap fonts
        assetManager.setLoader(FreeTypeFontGenerator.class, new FreeTypeFontGeneratorLoader(resolver));
        assetManager.setLoader(BitmapFont.class, ".ttf", new FreetypeFontLoader(resolver));

        FreeTypeFontLoaderParameter fontParams = new FreeTypeFontLoaderParameter();

        fontParams.fontFileName = "Jet Set.ttf";
        fontParams.fontParameters.size = 48;

        String fontName="Jet Set.ttf.48.ttf";

        assetManager.load(fontName, BitmapFont.class, fontParams);

        assetManager.finishLoading();

        BitmapFont bitmapFont=assetManager.get(fontName, BitmapFont.class);

        Gdx.app.log("FontDebugging", "fontName=" + fontName);
        Gdx.app.log("FontDebugging", "bitmapFont=" + bitmapFont);
    }
```

The last log line causes an assert from calling BitmapFont.toString().
